FinTech Transaction Analysis

Project Overview

This project analyzes 10,000 financial transactions to identify spending patterns, revenue trends, and customer purchasing behavior.

The goal of this analysis was to apply data analytics techniques to transform raw transactional data into meaningful business insights using Python.

---

Project Author : Esihle Mkhusane  
Role: Data Analyst

As the Data Analyst on this project, I was responsible for:

- Data loading and validation  
- Data cleaning and transformation  
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)  
- Revenue and customer behavior analysis  
- Data visualization using Matplotlib  
- Extracting actionable business insights  

---

Tools & Technologies Used

- Python
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- Jupyter Notebook (VS Code)
- Git & GitHub

---

Project Structure

---

Key Analysis Performed

Data Exploration
- Checked dataset structure and data types
- Verified missing values
- Generated summary statistics
- Verified absence of missing values

Data Transformation
- Converted transaction dates to datetime format
- Created monthly period column for time-series analysis

Revenue Analysis
- Calculated total revenue
- Computed Average Transaction Value (ATV)
- Analyzed monthly revenue trends

Customer Insights
- Identified top 10 customers by total spend
- Evaluated purchasing behavior

Product & Category Insights
- Determined most purchased items
- Analyzed revenue contribution by category

Payment Behavior
- Examined distribution of payment methods used by customers

---

Key Insights

- The dataset contains complete transaction data with no missing values.
- Revenue trends show consistent transactional activity.
- A small group of customers contributes significantly to total revenue.
- Certain categories generate higher revenue than others.
- Digital payment methods dominate transaction activity.

